      • getDataSourceTimestamp

        public long getDataSourceTimestamp(CmsRequest<PE> request)
        Get the latest timestamp of the data being used to generate the content. The timestamp should be for the content being generated by the generator. The timestamp should not represent data from other elements in the process chain with the exception of delegates not processed by CMS. This method is guaranteed to be called for every CMS (http / servlet) request.

        Returns the last modified time of the PageElement.

        Specified by:
        getDataSourceTimestamp in interface Generator<PE extends PageElement>
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the timestamp or -1 if unknown.

      • getExpireTime

        public long getExpireTime()
        Get the expire time of the generated content. This method must never return a negative value. Content generators must always specify a valid expire time.

        A default is used if the expire time is set to Integer.MIN_VALUE or unset. The default is based on the value returned by HTMLPageElementUtil.getExpireTime(PageElement, java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit, long) with the last two parameters being TimeUnit.HOURS and 4. The default can only be calculated if subclasses call one of these methods: getIdentity(CmsRequest), getDataSourceTimestamp(CmsRequest), preRenderProcess(CmsRequest, CmsResponse, ProcessChain), or calculateDefaultExpireTime(CmsRequest).

        Specified by:
        getExpireTime in interface Cacheable<PE extends PageElement>
        Specified by:
        getExpireTime in interface Generator<PE extends PageElement>
        Returns:
        the expire time in millis or 0 if it expires immediately. Return -1 to indicate that the expire time from this Cacheable shouldn't be used unless otherwise specified.

      • getIdentity

        public String getIdentity(CmsRequest<PE> request)
        Return a string that uniquely identifies the information needed to generate or influence the content for the response.

        For example, if the response is dependent on a record from the database, an implementor should return a String representing the database key and a timestamp for when the record was last updated.

        Returns the last modified time of the PageElement.

        Specified by:
        getIdentity in interface Cacheable<PE extends PageElement>
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the identity of the generated content or null if unknown / unimplemented.
